    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what the text says to what it means in its original context and its place in the canon. Genesis 47 is a narrative chapter, not an epistle; its theology is embedded in plot, character, and juxtaposition rather than in propositional statements. The movements below trace the chapter's argument as it develops from diplomatic settlement through famine administration to deathbed covenant. Where the Hebrew vocabulary illuminates the English, a brief note follows.",
